00:41:24,880 --> 00:41:25,359
>> Yeah.

687
00:41:25,359 --> 00:41:32,079
And so I think related to being a sturdy leader to make it more concrete, there's two jobs we have as a parent.

688
00:41:32,079 --> 00:41:35,760
I think they're the same two jobs we have as any sturdy leader in any environment.

689
00:41:35,760 --> 00:41:41,200
And that's setting boundaries, which are limits we set, certain decisions we make.

690
00:41:41,200 --> 00:41:52,240
Boundaries often relate to your position of authority where you have some long-term goal in mind that someone else in the system just isn't as aware of or a two-year-old isn't as capable of holding on to which is why you're in the

691
00:41:52,240 --> 00:41:53,599
position of making a decision.

692
00:41:53,599 --> 00:42:01,520
So that's the boundaries and the other side is validating kids or someone else's experience while not being taken over by it.

693
00:42:01,520 --> 00:42:05,280
And I think we've moved so far in this direction of validating kids experience.

694
00:42:05,280 --> 00:42:11,599
And I'll go on record and saying validating kids feelings is an incomplete parenting approach.

695
00:42:11,599 --> 00:42:13,599
That is that is half of our job.

696
00:42:13,599 --> 00:42:21,359
