718
00:43:35,440 --> 00:43:36,240
Everyone.

719
00:43:36,240 --> 00:43:37,119
Okay.

720
00:43:37,119 --> 00:43:42,160
And with my other kids, one of them especially, I probably would have been able to make a request like,

721
00:43:42,160 --> 00:43:45,599
"Hey, when we go in the elevator later, it's really important not to press all the buttons.

722
00:43:45,599 --> 00:43:46,960
Other people wait for this elevator.

723
00:43:46,960 --> 00:43:52,319
It's rude, whatever it is, that's not a boundary because I could say, did I tell my kid what I will do?

724
00:43:52,319 --> 00:43:53,040
No.

725
00:43:53,040 --> 00:43:54,800
Does it require my kid to do nothing?

726
00:43:54,800 --> 00:43:55,359
No.

727
00:43:55,359 --> 00:43:56,079
Okay.

728
00:43:56,079 --> 00:44:00,160
A boundary would be saying when we go into the elevator, I'm going to stand between you and the buttons,

729
00:44:00,160 --> 00:44:04,160
sweetie, because I'm not going to let you press the buttons cuz other people are waiting.

730
00:44:04,160 --> 00:44:07,839
And if you have a kid, like my kid, they're going to lunge for it anyway.

731
00:44:07,839 --> 00:44:11,520
And then I would block my kid because I'm ready and I've done a workout.

732
00:44:11,520 --> 00:44:12,480
My muscles are ready.

733
00:44:12,480 --> 00:44:13,920
I'm not going to let you do that.

734
00:44:13,920 --> 00:44:17,680
Now, my kid might get upset, which allows me to do the other part of my jobs.

735
00:44:17,680 --> 00:44:23,280
Gh, I know you wish you could press those buttons, or maybe just look kindly toward him and not say anything,

736
00:44:23,280 --> 00:44:26,319
but I'm going to still hold my boundary.

737
00:44:26,319 --> 00:44:31,359
And in this example, I think one of the places we get into trouble as a parent is we say,

738
00:44:31,359 --> 00:44:33,119
"Don't press the buttons.

739
00:44:33,119 --> 00:44:38,079
If you press the buttons, no dessert tonight," or whatever, we like threaten.

740
00:44:38,079 --> 00:44:45,280
But all of that is a way of completely undermining our authority because I'm giving all of my power to my kid.

741
00:44:45,280 --> 00:44:47,680
I'm letting myself get frustrated.

742
00:44:47,680 --> 00:44:49,200
Now I'm taking away dessert.

743
00:44:49,200 --> 00:44:57,359
And the honest truth, if we want to be honest about it, is at night I'm going to give my kid sorbet anyway and then make up something how sorbet isn't dessert because it has fruit.

744
00:44:57,359 --> 00:45:00,400
All because I just didn't set a boundary in the first place.

745
00:45:00,400 --> 00:45:10,000
And I think over and over in parenting, maybe at work too, we're asking our kid to do our job for us because we just don't want to deal

